         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">St Andrews College, Sandhurst ¶ 4/8/85 ¶ Dear Sir ¶  ¶ Accept my sincere thanks for the lists &amp; extracts. ¶  ¶ I have sent on your request to my correspondent at Wagga; ¶  I have written to our Presby...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">85.08.04</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Robert Thom</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Linnean Society, London, Archives, Guard Book 1880-85, f. 303.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">St Andrews College, Sandhurst<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Now Bendigo, Vic.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">4/8/85</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Accept my sincere thanks for the lists &amp; extracts.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have sent on your request to my correspondent at Wagga;<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>NSW.</p>
               </note> I have written to our Presbyterian Minister at Silverton<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>NSW</p>
               </note> &amp; also to others about collecting plants. I do not think that our Church Periodical circulates in S. Australia, but if I can hear of any one likely to help I shall write him privately. I have got many promises but they come to little.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have written several times to the Sec. of Lin. Soc, but can get no reply. A brother at home at last got receipt for my last subscription which he sent to me. I got a friend to call for such publications as were due to me – but the Sec. put him off with the reply <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">that he would see about it</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style="font-style: italic; ">.</seg> I wrote again last March instructing the Sec. to send my publications through the same agent as sends Dr McGillivray’s of this town – but no reply. Should my bookseller at home call for them – the friend who called had a written note from me. I am very sorry to trespass on your valuable time, but if you can suggest to me what I should do, you will much oblige.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to B. D. Jackson, 9 August 1885 (in this edition as 85-08-09a). M has annotated Thom’s letter “Answ 9/8/85”, but the letter to Thom has not been found.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Yours sincerely</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>R Thom</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">I have sent on the seeds of <name key="Euchlaena">Euchlaena</name> to several squatters. The plant does not endure the frosts of Sandhurst. My plants do not ripen – perhaps they were sown too late, but from the plants that grew with me, it is evidently a first rate forage plant.<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M provides an extensive entry for <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Euchlaena">Euchlaena</name>
                     </seg> in all editions of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Select extra-tropical plants</seg>, first under <seg style="font-style: italic; ">E. luxurians</seg> and then <seg style="font-style: italic; ">E. mexicana.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Euchlaena">Euchlaena</name>
            </p>
         </div>
